HEADWORD: Atomistic
<hw>At`om*is"tic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to atoms; relating to atomism.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is the object of the mechanical <qex>atomistic</qex> philosophy
to confound synthesis with synartesis.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>divided into separate and often disparate elements;
-- the opposite of <ant>holistic</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> atomistical.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>atomistical</ent>⟦br⟧
